{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":141579,"duration_api_ms":139159,"num_turns":28,"result":"The fix is complete. Here's a summary:\n\n## Summary\n\n**Problem**: The `protect` method in `LocalTree` was not ignoring `EPERM` and `EACCES` errors from `os.chmod`, which caused failures in shared cache scenarios where the user might not own the cache files.\n\n**Solution**: Modified the `protect` method in `dvc/tree/local.py` to catch `OSError` exceptions and silently return when the error is `EPERM` or `EACCES`.\n\n**Changes made**:\n- Added a try-except block around the `chmod` call in the `protect` method\n- When `OSError` with `errno.EPERM` or `errno.EACCES` is caught, the method returns normally instead of raising\n- Other errors are still properly propagated\n\nThis fix aligns with PR #5335's requirement to ignore errors on `protect` operations in shared cache scenarios.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"e29157c6-5d21-4e54-8a04-cb5b4e5b3d7b","total_cost_usd":0.7009215,"usage":{"input_tokens":190538,"cache_creation_input_tokens":438,"cache_read_input_tokens":91950,"output_tokens":6672,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"cache_deleted_input_tokens":0,"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed":{"inputTokens":190538,"outputTokens":6672,"cacheReadInputTokens":91950,"cacheCreationInputTokens":438,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.7009215,"contextWindow":196000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"97a36285-69a9-4b1e-a7c7-d6acebe4502d"}
